eams dirty and muddled. Similarly to the guttural, there is no change to the distortion mechanism. Starting with a high scream, make the vowels more front and more close, around [i] or [ɨ]. Usually, the tongue is also much farther forward than for a typical vowel, so it could be described as a syllabic alveolar approximant. Again, the nature of the sound comes from the vowel overtones, which clash with the distorted voice to make the specific tone.%0a%3c %0a%3c This information is consciously used by death metal vocalists. The Youtube channel Kardavox Academy does videos analyzing death metal vocals, and the phonetic nature of vowels has been mentioned there several times.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
